You are implementing a shipment tracking Blazor Web App. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-173687b0b6844828a5a81fbcb6de5a31/ShipmentTracker/` with Interactive Auto global mode and Individual auth.

Project structure:
- `ShipmentTracker/` - server project (hosts app, EF Core, Identity)
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - client project (interactive components, pages)

Key rules for Auto global mode:
- ALL interactive components/pages go in the `.Client` project
- Components cannot access DbContext directly - must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there
- Server project implements same interface with direct DB access
- Both Program.cs must register matching services

## What to implement:

### 1. Remove template pages
Delete these files from `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/`:
- `Counter.razor`
- `Weather.razor`

Keep `Home.razor`, `Auth.razor`, `NotFound.razor`.

### 2. Create shared model in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed
}
```

### 3. Create service interface in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<Shipment?> UpdateStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus newStatus);
}
```

### 4. Client-side implementation using HttpClient

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService : IShipmentService
{
    private readonly HttpClient _http;

    public ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http)
    {
        _http = http;
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await _http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await _http.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> UpdateStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus newStatus)
    {
        var response = await _http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", newStatus);
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }
}
```

